<a href="http://www.aei-desis.net/">Aei'Desis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufaengsway.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FaengSway</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(5/2/01 2:26:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=207.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can Mages Solo with the best of them ?</span><hr size=1> We do, in our own way.  Mages need to kill LOW LOW blues by the hundreds.  Where necros will fear kite high blues and yellows, we will be mowing down every thing we see.<br>
<br>
Find the lowest blue you can find and make your best fire pet and watch it solo it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usilverbladetheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(5/2/01 2:29:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=207.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/excaliburthumb1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can Mages Solo with the best of them ?</span><hr size=1> Well, it really is a point of finding the RIGHT targets and the RIGHT spots. This is vital! There's an area behind the fort in Frontier Mountains like an ampitheatre, from around 29-35 it is SUPERB.<br>
  But you really have to figure out what/how to pull/tactics yourself. I liked useing pull to fire pet...nuke or malise, stand behind the pet so mobsgets locked on pet and frenzies, then nuke when mob has takens say 30%+ damage. ALso you must have SOW, buy potions, befriend druids they appreciate lev rings coldstones etc.<br>
