<br>
    Your pets are simply meat shields between you and a mob.  A 51 earth pet is a massive meat shield (3000ish hps) that also does decent damage.<br>
<br>
     Cast your pet and DON'T spend mana buffing it.  Just send him in and med as soon as it is safe to do so.  If you regain enough mana to cast a new pet before the pet dies, you can effectively recast pets until you run out of malachite or until the mob is dead.<br>
<br>
    I soloed Quag Maelstrom in the Ocean of Tears (level 45 Seafury who procs a mana drain.  He has approx 8000 hps)  At the end of my fight I had lost a total of 20m and was immediately ready to pull any blue clops I could find.  It took about 4-6 level 51 pets to do it, and I didn't assist my pet in the least, except to cast another at the appropriate time.  I also soloed the Tainted Seafury Cyclops just to see if I could do it, and beat him down after probably 8-10 pets.  I ended that fight at approximately 50m or so.  I even tried the Corrupted...  and well...  I gated after he summoned me.. lol.<br>
<br>
    Malachite is the best investment a magician can make.  Invest a lot, it always pays you back many times over. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill>The Hunt</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
